values:
Kiri-Chan,

I warned my readers that my french was from an internet translator. I also apologized for any mistakes made because of that. Sorry to disappoint and make you angry. But the warning was there. I understand that it would make you angry to see your language wrong. But you needn't tell someone that it SUCKS. If an author tells me (as a reader) that they've got their english from an online translator and it is, infact, not they're mother tongue, I'm not going to tell them that they're english sucks. Yes, I understand that it's a bit hard to read when the grammar/word is wrong, but it's just the same when someone does that with english. You just politely correct them, that's all. No need to get hasty.

New journal, new fandom, new OTP. Okay, in Harry Potter my OTP = REMUS/SIRIUS. In PotC my OTP = TURROW! Which of course is Jack Sparrow/Will Turner ship. YAY! Now I'm working on a Turrow at the moment. But I don't know exactly when it will be finished. Also I got bit by a plot bunny while watching T.V. so there will be more. I'm just not sure when that will be out either. Oh! There's another one. Hehe. Don't know when it will be out either. ::sighs::
